The paper deals with the construction of short descriptions of strings, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The technique used involves compression and the construction of succinct data structures, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of Kolmogorov complexity, which is a measure of randomness and a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
